{"cursor":"20911","size":15,"audio":["http://download.omroep.nl/rnw/smac/podcast/audio/all_channels/en_radiobooks_20090211_44_1kHz_20090216_134724.mp3","http://download.omroep.nl/rnw/smac/podcast/audio/all_channels/en_radiobooks_20090211_44_1kHz_20090216_134724.mp3"],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox writer\n| birth_name = Eric Firmin Petrus de Kuyper birth_date = birth_place = Brussels,\n| Belgium occupation = Novelist, filmmaker, semiologist language = Dutch\n| (Flemish), French, English, German ethnicity = Flemish citizenship = Belgian\n| education = PhD (EHESS) alma_mater = Rits, Erasmushogeschool Brussel; Vrije\n| Universiteit Brussel; Ãcole des hautes Ã©tudes en sciences sociales, Paris\n| period = 1980sâpresent genre = Autobiographical novel, [[Bildungsroman]],\n| mystery, short story, screenplay; essay, academic non-fiction, art criticism,\n| reviews subject = 3rd-person autobiography, human condition; semiotics,\n| cinema, dance, homosexuality partner = Emile Poppe Lommel, Belgium\n| influences = Marcel Proust, Roland Barthes, Algirdas Julien Greimas awards =\n| portaldisp = y\n}}\n\n'Eric de Kuyper' is a Flemish-Belgian and Dutch writer, semiologist, art critic,\nand experimental film director. Fictionalized autobiographical novels, written\nin the 3rd-person, account for most of his creative work. His academic writing\nencompasses reviews, essays, articles, and books on semiotics, film, dance,\ntheater, and opera. His non-traditional films reveal an engineered penchant for\nmelodrama, love songs, and silent movies, their central topic is homosexuality.\nTowards the end of the 2000s, he started organizing concerts en images, events\nin which he combines silent films, some segments shot by himself for the\noccasions, with live classical music, and sometimes singing and acting.\n","linknr":312,"url":"Eric_de_Kuyper","recorded":1375059554,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Eric_de_Kuyper&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Eric_de_Kuyper&action=edit","//bit